In Ethiopia, there are many students who are eager to participate in debates and panel discussions, but the current system limits them to intra-school activities only. To address this gap, I want to create a digital debate platform that connects and invites nearby schools into regular competitions and panel discussions. My plan is to first establish a debate club at my school, then invite students from other schools to join and participate. This initiative will give students more opportunities to develop critical thinking by analyzing different perspectives, improve public speaking by expressing their ideas clearly, and strengthen teamwork by working together to build strong arguments. By creating this platform, I hope to encourage collaboration among schools and give students a space to confidently share ideas and learn from one another. rate this
